revision.text:
The '''New York Dance and Performance Awards''', also known as the '''Bessie Awards''' are awarded annually for exceptional achievement by independent dance artists presenting their work in New York City. The broad categories of the awards are: choreography, performance, music composition and visual design. The Bessie Awards were established in 1983.
==History and description== The Bessie Awards were established in 1983 by [[Dance Theater Workshop]] and named in honor of [[Bessie Schonberg]], an influential mid-20th-century teacher of modern dance and former head of the dance department at Sarah Lawrence College.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dunning|first1=Jennifer|title='Bessies' to Be Awarded Sept. 13 for Achievement in Dance|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1984/08/20/arts/bessies-to-be-awarded-sept-13-for-achievements-in-dance.html|accessdate=17 October 2017|publisher=New York Times|date=20 August 1984}}</ref>. The awards honor exceptional choreography, performance, music composition and visual design in dance and allied art forms.<ref name=about /> Nominees and award winners are chosen by the Bessie Selection Committee, which consists of dancers, dance presenters, producers, choreographers, journalists, critics and academics.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/09/11/arts/dance/11bessies.html |title=Bessies Are Back After a Hiatus, Primed for a Major Makeover |work= [[The New York Times]]|date=10 September 2010| first= Gia| last= Kourlas| accessdate= 18 August 2012}}</ref>
Since 2010, the awards have been overseen by an independent steering committee in partnership with Dance/NYC and administered by [[Lucy Sexton]].<ref name="about">{{cite web|title=About the Bessies|url=http://bessies.org/about/|website=The Bessies|accessdate=17 October 2017}}</ref> In their current iteration, the awards encompass a broader range of dance genres and supporting art forms than in the past, and offer an annual commission to an emerging artist.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/12/arts/dance/bessies-new-categories-limit-definitions-of-dance.html |title=Classifications in the Science of an Art |work= [[The New York Times]]| date= 10 August 2012| first=Gia|last=Kourlas|accessdate=15 August 2013}}</ref>
==Recipients== Over 400 Bessie Awards have been presented since their founding. Notable recipients include:
