'''Chez Ntemba''' is a chain of [[nightclub]]s owned by [[Democratic Republic of the Congo|Congolese]] [[Augustin Kayembe]]. The first Chez Ntemba nightclub was founded in 1992 in [[Lusaka]]. {{As of|2014}} there are 41 night clubs all across sub-Saharan Africa.<ref>{{Cite news | title=Augustin Kayembe: The king of the African club scene | last=Mthembu-Salter | first=Gregory | date=31 October 2013 | newspaper=[[Mail & Guardian]] | url=http://mg.co.za/article/2013-10-31-augustin-kayembe-the-king-of-the-african-club-scene}}</ref> In June 2016, Chez Ntemba, hosted a music concert in the [[Kabulonga]] suburb of Lusaka.<ref>{{Cite web|title=VIP Chez Ntemba to host music concert | last=Phiri | first=Sam | url=http://www.times.co.zm/?p=86727 | newspaper=[[Times of Zambia]] | language=en-US | date=25 June 2016}}</ref>

