{{Infobox company | name = Fantawild | logo =Fantawild.svg | logo_caption = | image = | image_caption = | trading_name = <!-- d/b/a/, doing business as - if different from legal name above --> | native_name = <!-- Company's name in home country language --> | native_name_lang = <!-- Use ISO 639-2 code, e.g. "fr" for French. If there is more than one native name, in different languages, enter those names using {{tl|lang}}, instead. --> | type = | traded_as = | industry = [[Amusement park]]s | genre = <!-- Only used with media and publishing companies --> | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | founder = | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | area_served = [[China]] | key_people = | products = | production = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = <!-- Only used with financial services companies --> | assets = | equity = | owner = Huaqiang Group | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | footnotes = | intl = | romanized = | former type = | foundation = [[Chongqing]], [[China]] (2005 or 2007) | location_city = | location_country = | locations = 11 | homepage = {{URL|http://www.fantawild.com/en/index.html|www.fantawild.com}} | bodystyle = }}
'''Fantawild''' ('''Fangte''' in Chinese) is a chain of [[amusement park]]s located in various cities of [[China]]. The first park opened in the mid-to-late 2000s in [[Chongqing]]. {{As of|November 2013}}, ten amusement parks operate under the Fantawild name, with a further park currently under construction. The chain is owned by the Huaqiang Group.<ref name="Hi-tech parks open in China">{{cite journal|title=Hi-tech parks open in China |journal=Park World Magazine |date=18 December 2007 |url=http://www.parkworld-online.com/news/archivestory.php/aid/677/Hi-tech_parks_open_in_China.html |accessdate=21 November 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203045334/http://www.parkworld-online.com/news/archivestory.php/aid/677/Hi-tech_parks_open_in_China.html |archivedate=3 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> The mascot of the parks is a blue dinosaur named DuLuDuBi, and is typically used as the public image for the chain.
