{{Lowercase title}} {{Infobox company |name=iBAHN |logo = iBAHN-logo.jpeg |type=Privately held corporation |location_city=[[South Jordan, Utah]] |foundation=1998<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20101203232310/http://ibahn.com/en-us/index.php?cid=1609 ibahn.com]</ref> |homepage={{URL|www.ibahn.com}} |industry = [[Internet Service Provider]], [[Hospitality]]| |num_employees = 400<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibahn.com/en-us/public/docs/iBAHN-Co_Fact_Sheet.pdf|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101204000722/http://ibahn.com/en-us/public/docs/iBAHN-Co_Fact_Sheet.pdf|dead-url=yes|archive-date=December 4, 2010|title=iBAHN Corporation Factsheet|accessdate=February 17, 2011}}</ref> }}
'''iBAHN''' is a global provider of digital information and entertainment systems for the hospitality and meeting industries. They have approximately 400 employees spread over 17 regional offices throughout [[North America]], [[Asia]] and [[Europe]]. They offer services to more than 3,000 hotels in 40+ countries.<ref name=autogenerated1 /> In March 2014, following Chapter 11 Bankruptcy proceedings, the company was purchased by rival [[Guest-tek]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Guest-tek Acquisition of iBAHN Takes Hotel Technology to a Higher Level|url=http://hospitalitytechnology.edgl.com/news/Guest-tek-Acquisition-of-iBAHN-Takes-Hotel-Technology-to-a-Higher-Level91762|accessdate=25 March 2014}}</ref>
==History== iBAHN (originally called STSN, or Suite Technology Systems Network) was founded in February 1998 as an [[ISP]] focused on providing high-speed wired and wireless Internet service to hotels. Their first major client was Marriott Corporation, who signed a deal in 1999 to have STSN install high-speed Internet services in roughly 500 hotels.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=NewsLibrary&p_multi=DSNB&d_place=DSNB&p_theme=newslibrary2&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0F364F3378103D63&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM |title=Marriott offers fast Internet access |date=September 9, 1999 |accessdate=February 17, 2011 }}</ref>
In December 2002, STSN announced that they were one of several firms invested in by Intel Communications Fund in order to "accelerate Intel voice and data communications and wireless networking initiatives."<ref>{{cite news |author=Bob Brewin |url=http://www.computerworld.com/s/article/76876/Intel_invests_in_Wi_Fi_VOIP_and_hotel_access_companies |title=Intel invests in Wi-Fi VOIP and hotel-access companies |date=December 18, 2002 |accessdate=February 17, 2011 }}</ref> A substantial portion of this investment went towards the installation of WiFi services in nearly 400 Marriott hotels.<ref>{{cite news |url = http://www.m-travel.com/news/2002/12/marriott_launch.html |title = Marriott launches wireless access at 400 hotels |date = December 18, 2002 |accessdate = February 17, 2011 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110714010820/http://www.m-travel.com/news/2002/12/marriott_launch.html |archivedate = July 14, 2011 |df = }}</ref>
Rebranded as iBahn in 2005,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.law360.com/articles/470886/hotel-internet-provider-wins-ok-for-1-5m-ch-11-loan|title=Hotel Internet Provider Wins OK For $1.5M Ch. 11 Loan|accessdate=February 26, 2016|date=September 9, 2013}}</ref> the company has seen rapid expansion and has since expanded their product offering to include client and guest services and augmented conference and meeting solutions. They have also expanded their client base from strictly hotels and hospitality to corporate and government campuses and events.{{citation needed|date=February 2016}}
Current clients include [[Bank of America]], Boeing Travel Group, [[eBay]], [[General Electric]], [[IBM]], [[Intel Corporation]], [[Kraft Foods]], [[Marriott International Inc.]], [[McDonald’s Corporation]], [[Microsoft]], [[Quantum Corporation|Quantum]], [[State Farm Insurance]], [[U.S. Army]], [[Trident Hotels]] and [[Verizon]].{{citation needed|date=February 2016}}
Investors include [[Siemens]], On Command (now [[LodgeNet]]), [[Marriott International Inc.]], [[Intel Corp.]], [[Vantage Point Venture Partners]], APV Technology Partners, and ThomVest Holdings Inc.{{citation needed|date=February 2016}}
==Products== iBAHN produces a line of IP platform-based solutions for the hospitality and meeting industries in addition to "high-speed" wired and wireless Internet service.
